<subSubSection id="F4242FCF3199C75DB6854C425DA93539" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" type="description">
<paragraph id="771BFFDCA1EC9A225745B35790BA5A6B" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B828897A85781DF2127F6BF2C7DDA400" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">
Small undershrub to c. 25 cm, stems and branches sericeous, spinescent, sterile cauline spines present, few. Leaves sessile, 1.5-3 
<normalizedToken id="8C3677CDE2F39DE2E3856B7C136D71DC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 cm, obovate or elliptic, obtuse, entire, the base attenuate to a petiole-like base, densely sericeous. Flowers in compact capitate cymes, terminal on naked peduncle-like branches; bracts ovate, acuminate, densely pilose; bracteoles c. 8 
<normalizedToken id="0BC6B452FD1C40E7A905D0C3164B32B0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm, linear-lanceolate, finely acuminate, densely pilose; pedicels absent; sepals 8-9 
<normalizedToken id="3D8ABE41872CE8D5890D591182126B7A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2.5 mm, lanceolate, acuminate, pilose; corolla c. 1.8 mm long, cream, midpetaline bands pilose; ovary pilose; style pubescent, divided c. 5 mm above base, stigmas c. 3 mm. Capsule not seen. [
<bibRefCitation id="A7100C961BFD56DF787C109D6635310A" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="B78D5CCC1DA76820B1CF7C6346AF8858" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 85; 
<bibRefCitation id="B35DAD010407FED61B2F55D2583C8EB8" author="Nowroozi, M" journalOrPublisher="Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 110" refId="B244" refString="Nowroozi, M, 2002. Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae. Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran: 1 - 110" title="Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae" year="2002">Nowroozi 2002</bibRefCitation>
: 37 (plate), 101 (map), 
<bibRefCitation id="15FDA59D573C09435E11E0D0D2DC5594" author="Rechinger, KH" editor="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 24" refId="B298" refString="Rechinger, KH, 1963. Convolvulaceae. In: Rechinger, KH, Ed., Flora Iranica. Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz: 1 - 24" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Iranica." year="1963">Rechinger 1963</bibRefCitation>
: Figure 
<figureCitation id="54B9FADDF0E818B80B4982F8D822D3BB" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. 1 - 9 Convolvulus scammonia 1 leaves 2 bracteole 3 outer sepal 4 middle sepal 5 inner sepal 6 stamen 7 ovary and style 8 capsule 9 seed. 1 from Bourgeau 114 (W) 2 - 7 from Gathorne-Hardy 547 (E) 8 - 9 from Rechinger 10708 (W) 10 - 18 Convolvulus durandoi 10 leaves 11 bracteole 12 outer sepal 13 middle sepal 14 inner sepal 15 stamen 16 ovary and style 17 capsule 18 seed 10 &amp; 17 - 18 from Battandier &amp; Trabut 9 (GOET) 11 - 16 from Gay 2792 (W) 19 - 27 Convolvulus arvensis 19 leaves 20 bracteole 21 outer sepal 22 middle sepal attached to pedicel 23 inner sepal 24 stamen 25 ovary and style 26 capsule, 27 seed 19 - 25 from Abdallah et al. 1725 (CAIM) 26 - 27 from Abdallah et al. 1671 (CAIM) 28 - 33 Convolvulus chinensis 28 leaves 29 outer sepal 30 inner sepal 31 stamen 32 ovary and style 33 sepals enclosing capsule 28 (centre / right) from sin coll. 12 / 6 / 1886 (OXF) 28 (left) - 33 from Wang 3259 (K) 34 - 39 Convolvulus mairei 34 leaf 35 outer sepal 36 middle sepal 37 inner sepal 38 stamen 39 ovary and style. From Maire &amp; Petitmengin 628 (K) 40 - 48 Convolvulus fatmensis 40 leaves 41 bracteole 42 outer sepal 43 middle sepal 44 inner sepal 45 stamen 46 ovary and style 47 capsule 48 seed 40 - 46 from Schimper 839 (L) 47 - 48 from Shalaby &amp; Sharobiem 1637 (CAIM)." pageId="160" pageNumber="161">3</figureCitation>
]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BC778BBDD205C5B2083A5F4726E43AA7" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7B787761FC539ED5F3ABCAE1C50624A1" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39038CF60C21BC38B0412CD8E6400B02" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">
Endemic to southeastern Iran (
<emphasis id="8430E2984EEF98A1DDFCBC998B7C73C9" italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Popov</emphasis>
51/157, 
<emphasis id="37C7BF4D130DA4BE0DDEC19FD93A3237" italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Rechinger</emphasis>
55064, 
<emphasis id="FD62BB5172C8B1C80B08E266CD9C1373" italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Mirzayan</emphasis>
830E, 
<emphasis id="6E445955EBE5E215ECD723BAB0EBB56D" italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Assadi in Rechinger</emphasis>
54802, 
<emphasis id="EC9A6261AA684782C5E574D955D21372" italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Runemark et al.</emphasis>
22616).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3413FD718BEFB8CEABE707FE009A893E" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" type="notes">
<paragraph id="CD09D31B871BB03484D8425C9710AA6E" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="01A18CBC50D236EF7DE5C1978D0251A2" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">
Superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName id="5DF4D6B22968A979862FA5A6327838F4" authorityName="Boiss. Diagn. Pl. Orient 7: 23. 1846. (Boissier" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus oxysepalus" order="Solanales" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxysepalus">
<emphasis id="B0A4A5FBCF53FA725101D033DB60B7BC" italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Convolvulus oxysepalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the stem and leaves greyish-sericeous with adpressed hairs, the plant more obviously spiny with short-lateral spinescent branchlets in addition to the spinescent main shoots; the ovary is densely pilose and the style thinly pubescent, the stigmas only 3 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
